# Trivy ignore file for persons-finder
# These CVEs require upgrading to Spring Boot 3.x / Spring Framework 6.x.
# Tracked in backlog: migrate to Spring Boot 3.x + JDK 17.

# spring-web: "HttpInvokerServiceExporter" deserialization - Spring team marks this wontfix
# in 5.x; fix requires Spring 6.0+. This app does NOT use HttpInvokerServiceExporter.
CVE-2016-1000027

# spring-boot: actuator endpoint matcher bug - fixed in 3.3.11 / 3.4.5 only
CVE-2025-22235

# spring-core: annotation detection vulnerability - fixed in 6.2.11 only
CVE-2025-41249

# spring-webmvc: path traversal in RouterFunctions - fixed in 6.1.13 only
CVE-2024-38816

# spring-webmvc: path traversal in functional web frameworks - fixed in 6.1.14 only
CVE-2024-38819

# jackson-core: number length constraint bypass - fixed in 2.18.6+ which is incompatible
# with Spring Boot 2.7.x BOM; upgrading risks runtime breakage
GHSA-72hv-8253-57qq

# snakeyaml: Constructor deserialization RCE - fixed in 2.0 which has breaking API changes
# incompatible with Spring Boot 2.7.x; Spring Boot uses SafeConstructor (not vulnerable code path)
CVE-2022-1471

# ── pii-redaction-sidecar: Go stdlib CVEs (gobinary) ──────────────────────────
# These CVEs are embedded in the compiled sidecar binary (Go 1.25.x stdlib).
# Fix versions (Go 1.25.7 / 1.24.13) have been announced but are NOT YET
# published to Docker Hub. golang:1.25 currently resolves to v1.25.5.
# REMOVE these entries once golang:1.25.7+ is available on Docker Hub.
#
# 这些 CVE 编译进了 sidecar 二进制（Go 1.25.x stdlib）。
# 修复版本已公布但尚未推送到 Docker Hub（golang:1.25 = v1.25.5）。
# 待 golang:1.25.7+ 可用时移除以下条目。

# CVE-2025-68121 — CRITICAL — crypto/tls: Unexpected session resumption
# Fixed in Go 1.24.13 / 1.25.7. Exploitable only by a malicious TLS server;
# sidecar's upstream (api.openai.com) is a controlled, trusted endpoint.
CVE-2025-68121

# CVE-2025-61726 — HIGH — net/url: Memory exhaustion in query parameter parsing
# Fixed in Go 1.24.12 / 1.25.6. Input to the sidecar comes from the trusted
# main app container (localhost), not directly from external users.
CVE-2025-61726

# CVE-2025-61728 — HIGH — archive/zip: Excessive CPU on building archive index
# No fix version published yet. Sidecar does NOT use archive/zip at all.
CVE-2025-61728

# CVE-2025-61730 — HIGH — TLS 1.3 handshake: messages split across records
# No fix version published yet. Sidecar's TLS upstream is api.openai.com only.
CVE-2025-61730
